+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S4-P01-T042 (Realtime/Catchup/Backfill three-lane scheduler + auto-pause; closes S4-P01; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Forty-second task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the last of S4-P01 (pausable/resumable backfill engine). Goal: three priority lanes (realtime, catchup, backfill) with auto-pause so the 2016+ history backfill can never starve the live front-line data. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; scheduler logic, not wired to the production cron. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/three_lane_scheduler.py (a schedule that serves realtime first, allocates catchup and backfill by quota, applies backpressure that pauses backfill then throttles catchup whenever the projected realtime freshness P95 would exceed the baseline by more than 20%, and a kill switch; plus project_p95 and stress_test), THREE_LANE_SPEC.md, and evidence/ADP-S4-P01-T042/stress_test_report.json. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P01-T042/test-results/scheduler_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): in every stress scenario the realtime freshness P95 stays within the baseline+20% ceiling and realtime is always fully served -- healthy 11.9, backfill pressure 11.8, heavy realtime burst 11.6, kill switch 10.8, all under the ceiling of 12; the backfill lane runs when healthy (3 of 3), is throttled under pressure (2 of 8), and auto-pauses on a realtime burst (0 of 6) so its grant decreases monotonically as pressure rises at 3, 2, 0; and the kill switch pauses backfill (0 of 5). This guarantees the decade backfill and live freshness coexist. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
